# GATK-SV
GATK-SV is a structural variation discovery pipeline for Illumina short-read whole-genome sequencing (WGS) data.
This workspace contains the GATK-SV joint calling pipeline; for the single-sample pipeline refer to [this workspace](https://app.terra.bio/#workspaces/help-gatk/GATK-Structural-Variants-Single-Sample).

Please refer to the GATK-SV [website](https://broadinstitute.github.io/gatk-sv/) for documentation.
The [joint calling pipeline execution page](https://broadinstitute.github.io/gatk-sv/docs/execution/joint) contains detailed information on this Terra workspace and how to apply the pipeline to your own data.

## Genomic Disorder CNV Calling

This workspace includes the `CallGenomicDisorderCNVs` workflow for detecting copy-number variants at known genomic disorder loci.
This workflow runs as a standalone post-processing step after `04-GatherBatchEvidence` completes.

| Attribute | Description |
|-----------|-------------|
| `gd_table` | Genomic disorder regions table (TSV) |
| `gd_segdup_bed` | Segmental duplication regions (BED) |
| `gd_centromere_bed` | Centromere regions (BED) |
| `gd_acrocentric_arm_bed` | Acrocentric chromosome arm regions (BED) |
| `gd_custom_mask_bed` | Custom masking regions (BED) |
| `gd_hard_inclusion_bed` | Hard inclusion intervals (BED) |
| `gd_gaps_bed` | Assembly gap regions (BED) |
| `gd_gtf` | Gene annotation (GTF) |

The workflow produces a single compressed output tarball (`gd_output_tarball`) containing:
- `gd_cnv_calls.tsv.gz` — Final GD CNV calls with scores
- `cn_posteriors.tsv.gz` — Per-bin copy-number posterior probabilities
- `viterbi_paths.tsv.gz` — Viterbi segmentation paths (when using viterbi calling mode)
- `bin_mappings.tsv.gz` — Bin-to-interval coordinate mappings
- `locus_intervals.tsv.gz` — Locus definitions with interval coordinates
- `gd_entry_intervals.tsv.gz` — GD entry to interval mappings
